-- BMW to Hire 4,000 on 2012 Growth Prospects, Automotive News Says
-- B y   S t e f a n   N i c o l a
-- 2012-03-11T13:13:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-11/bmw-to-hire-4-000-on-2012-growth-prospects-automotive-news-says.html
Bayerische Motoren Werke AG (BMW)  plans
to hire about 4,000 workers this year while expecting faster
growth than the global market,  Automotive News Europe  reported,
citing Chief Executive Officer  Norbert Reithofer .  The German automaker plans to hire about the same number of
employees in 2012 as last year, Reithofer was cited by the
magazine as saying. BMW took on about 4,000 people in 2011,
Automotive News  Europe  said, citing a company spokesman.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
 landberg@bloomberg.net  